80
01:24:35,339 --> 01:24:36,239
[SPEAKER_09]: All right, good evening.

81
01:24:36,299 --> 01:24:36,840
[SPEAKER_09]: My name is Ms.

82
01:24:36,860 --> 01:24:39,501
[SPEAKER_09]: Frank and I'm in charge of the Missituck Student Council.

83
01:24:39,901 --> 01:24:42,823
[SPEAKER_09]: The Student Council is a group of students elected by their classmates.

84
01:24:43,283 --> 01:24:48,386
[SPEAKER_09]: Our goal is to create a school community that is inclusive, respectful, and kind, where every student voice is heard.

85
01:24:49,186 --> 01:24:50,507
[SPEAKER_09]: This is the Missituck Student Council.

86
01:24:51,667 --> 01:24:55,229
[SPEAKER_09]: Starting with Treasurer Yara, Student Rep Vera, and Student Rep Val.

87
01:24:59,632 --> 01:25:00,192
[SPEAKER_09]: And next slide.

88
01:25:03,611 --> 01:25:10,295
[SPEAKER_27]: The Student Council of Mystic Elementary is a group of students elected by their classmates to represent their views and interests.

89
01:25:11,296 --> 01:25:18,380
[SPEAKER_26]: We are committed to promoting the principles of the school's culture and ensuring that every student's voice is heard.

90
01:25:20,765 --> 01:25:25,631
[SPEAKER_17]: Our goal is to create a school community that is inclusive, respectful, and kind.

91
01:25:26,191 --> 01:25:34,140
[SPEAKER_17]: Our student council does its best to ensure that student voices are heard and valued in all aspects of school life.

92
01:25:35,381 --> 01:25:35,822
[SPEAKER_09]: Next slide.

93
01:25:38,365 --> 01:25:41,168
[SPEAKER_09]: Secretary Addy, student rep Luke, student rep Lucas.

94
01:25:45,576 --> 01:25:57,478
[SPEAKER_24]: The Mississauga Student Council has one president, vice president, secretary, and treasurer from fifth grade, one class representative from each fourth grade class, and two class representatives from each fifth grade class.

95
01:26:00,017 --> 01:26:04,279
[SPEAKER_18]: As members of the student council, we have several responsibilities, including.

96
01:26:05,680 --> 01:26:25,571
[SPEAKER_16]: Representing the views and interests of our classmates, attending student council meetings, and contributing to discussions, working with our classmates and reporting back to them on the work of the student council, working on initiatives and projects that promote the values of our school, and supporting the school in creating an inclusive, kind, and respectful environment.

97
01:26:27,851 --> 01:26:29,693
[SPEAKER_09]: President Lillian, Vice President Nora.

98
01:26:34,999 --> 01:26:40,165
[SPEAKER_19]: We are responsible for creating and leading school-wide responsive classroom assembly.

99
01:26:41,287 --> 01:26:43,970
[SPEAKER_25]: This helps build public speaking confidence.

100
01:26:45,912 --> 01:26:46,393
[SPEAKER_25]: Luke and Lucas.

101
01:26:52,107 --> 01:26:59,130
[SPEAKER_24]: New Hampshire State Representative Dr. Jennifer Mandeboa has Monday, April 13th.

102
01:27:01,571 --> 01:27:09,254
[SPEAKER_18]: Professor of Public Health at Tufts, expert in community organization, listens to consensuance.

103
01:27:10,174 --> 01:27:11,515
[SPEAKER_18]: More speakers to come.

104
01:27:13,996 --> 01:27:14,356
[SPEAKER_09]: Yara.

105
01:27:21,300 --> 01:27:23,961
[SPEAKER_17]: We fundraised for two Gaga Pits.

106
01:27:24,461 --> 01:27:27,561
[SPEAKER_17]: We have raised $291 in direct donation.

107
01:27:28,081 --> 01:27:33,222
[SPEAKER_17]: We raised $1,002 in popcorn sales, but we only got to keep half.

108
01:27:33,803 --> 01:27:36,143
[SPEAKER_17]: We have raised enough money to reach our goal of $500.

109
01:27:36,203 --> 01:27:36,703
[SPEAKER_17]: Lily and Anora.

110
01:27:53,484 --> 01:27:57,427
[SPEAKER_19]: Each upper grade student is paired up with one or two lower grade students.

111
01:27:58,588 --> 01:28:01,511
[SPEAKER_25]: Students meet with their buddies twice a month.

112
01:28:02,051 --> 01:28:08,076
[SPEAKER_25]: Fifth grade is paired with second grade, fourth grade is paired with first grade, and third grade is paired with kindergarten.

113
01:28:10,158 --> 01:28:10,338
[SPEAKER_16]: Addie.

114
01:28:15,087 --> 01:28:16,168
[SPEAKER_16]: Buddies create belonging.

115
01:28:16,909 --> 01:28:20,932
[SPEAKER_16]: Meeting with buddies helps create a larger sense of belonging within Missittook community.

116
01:28:21,453 --> 01:28:24,055
[SPEAKER_16]: Wherever students are in the building, they will know someone.

117
01:28:24,956 --> 01:28:30,301
[SPEAKER_16]: I love how we get to meet with them and get to know them and help them learn from a fifth grade student.

118
01:28:32,123 --> 01:28:34,365
[SPEAKER_09]: Student reps Robley and student rep Trudeau.

119
01:28:39,999 --> 01:28:42,019
[SPEAKER_20]: Buddies belonging, poetry.

120
01:28:42,039 --> 01:28:46,720
[SPEAKER_20]: These are examples of buddies doing the poetry with their buddies in fifth grade.

121
01:28:49,841 --> 01:28:52,422
[SPEAKER_20]: Next slide.

122
01:28:52,582 --> 01:28:55,722
[SPEAKER_24]: These are examples of buddies doing poetry.

123
01:29:00,583 --> 01:29:04,084
[SPEAKER_20]: These are more pictures of buddies reading together.

124
01:29:04,664 --> 01:29:07,185
[SPEAKER_20]: These are fourth graders reading with their buddies.

125
01:29:22,572 --> 01:29:23,793
[SPEAKER_13]: Don't sit down yet.

126
01:29:23,873 --> 01:29:26,594
[SPEAKER_13]: I'm not sure if there are any questions before we take a picture.

127
01:29:36,520 --> 01:29:37,500
[SPEAKER_06]: Hello.

128
01:29:37,720 --> 01:29:42,003
[SPEAKER_06]: I just wanted to say I think it's amazing that you guys are starting doing this work.

129
01:29:42,023 --> 01:29:44,124
[SPEAKER_06]: So we're the high school student counselors.

130
01:29:44,144 --> 01:29:45,705
[SPEAKER_06]: We're non-voting members of the school committee.

131
01:29:45,725 --> 01:29:51,108
[SPEAKER_06]: We come up here and we sort of try and provide feedback on legislature, try to provide an opinion.

132
01:29:51,637 --> 01:29:57,504
[SPEAKER_06]: And we actually do presentations occasionally on student voice and sort of.

133
01:29:57,928 --> 01:30:00,209
[SPEAKER_06]: what opinions we gather through surveys and other means.

134
01:30:00,229 --> 01:30:01,289
[SPEAKER_06]: We're actually doing one tonight.

135
01:30:01,929 --> 01:30:05,170
[SPEAKER_06]: So it's super amazing to see that you guys are starting on this so early.

136
01:30:05,270 --> 01:30:07,651
[SPEAKER_06]: Please continue to do this throughout your school careers.

137
01:30:08,251 --> 01:30:10,552
[SPEAKER_06]: Stay informed, stay active.

138
01:30:10,932 --> 01:30:12,872
[SPEAKER_06]: This is really how we make a positive change.

139
01:30:12,932 --> 01:30:14,773
[SPEAKER_06]: It's really important, really inspiring.

140
01:30:14,813 --> 01:30:20,475
[SPEAKER_06]: And I bet you one of you might be sitting up in this seat in a few years.

141
01:30:20,595 --> 01:30:24,496
[SPEAKER_06]: So thank you so much for coming and for doing this.

142
01:30:32,133 --> 01:30:32,313
[SPEAKER_28]: Yeah.

143
01:30:32,614 --> 01:30:34,097
[SPEAKER_28]: Well, you've got our microphone.

144
01:30:34,557 --> 01:30:35,980
[SPEAKER_28]: What advice do you have for us?

145
