147
01:30:42,712 --> 01:30:44,315
[SPEAKER_28]: Not to put anyone on the spot, of course.

148
01:31:03,568 --> 01:31:03,728
[SPEAKER_09]: No?

149
01:31:06,431 --> 01:31:08,132
[SPEAKER_09]: They would like fewer standardized tests.

150
01:31:08,953 --> 01:31:09,453
[SPEAKER_09]: Okay.

151
01:31:12,936 --> 01:31:14,178
[SPEAKER_15]: Thank you, love that answer.

152
01:31:15,939 --> 01:31:16,359
[SPEAKER_15]: Thank you.

153
01:31:16,380 --> 01:31:17,160
[SPEAKER_15]: Okay, you want a picture?

154
01:31:21,584 --> 01:31:22,025
[SPEAKER_15]: No, okay.

155
01:31:22,045 --> 01:31:24,006
[SPEAKER_15]: Do you want them to come up?

156
01:31:24,607 --> 01:31:26,749
[SPEAKER_13]: So we're just going to have Ms.

157
01:31:26,849 --> 01:31:30,032
[SPEAKER_13]: Frank and the student council come in here for a quick picture.

158
01:31:31,010 --> 01:31:33,911
[SPEAKER_13]: That way the caregivers can get ready with their cameras.

159
01:32:53,498 --> 01:32:53,778
[SPEAKER_13]: All right.

160
01:32:55,019 --> 01:33:02,744
[SPEAKER_13]: Our next Mustang moment, we are going to have the advisors to the Unified Program at Medford High School come on up.

161
01:33:02,784 --> 01:33:06,187
[SPEAKER_13]: They're going to do some framing for this wonderful opportunity.

162
01:33:06,807 --> 01:33:11,130
[SPEAKER_13]: And they have some students with them that will be talking about their experiences in the program.

163
01:33:28,300 --> 01:33:30,502
[SPEAKER_11]: Hi everybody.

164
01:33:31,163 --> 01:33:33,765
[SPEAKER_05]: We are here to talk about Unified PE tonight.

165
01:33:35,227 --> 01:33:40,932
[SPEAKER_05]: Unified PE, much like Unified Sports, is an initiative set forth by the Special Olympics.

166
01:33:41,333 --> 01:33:50,742
[SPEAKER_05]: It brings students both with and without disabilities together to participate, in this case, in a PE, a physical education curriculum that is rooted in teamwork.

167
01:33:52,791 --> 01:33:55,852
[SPEAKER_29]: This is our third year, I think, doing it.

168
01:33:55,912 --> 01:33:57,892
[SPEAKER_29]: And we're really starting to hit our stride.

169
01:33:58,272 --> 01:34:00,433
[SPEAKER_29]: We have unbelievable kids, as you'll see in a second.

170
01:34:00,573 --> 01:34:02,333
[SPEAKER_29]: And our high school helper kids are great.

171
01:34:02,393 --> 01:34:03,834
[SPEAKER_29]: So it's not about us.

172
01:34:03,854 --> 01:34:04,334
[SPEAKER_29]: It's about them.

173
01:34:04,354 --> 01:34:05,834
[SPEAKER_29]: We're going to have them tell you all about it.

174
01:34:06,875 --> 01:34:10,856
[SPEAKER_05]: So we have Nolan, Ruby, Ella, Kelly, and Andrea up with us.

175
01:34:11,776 --> 01:34:12,716
[SPEAKER_05]: And you can take it away.

176
01:34:14,637 --> 01:34:14,797
Yeah.

177
01:34:19,298 --> 01:34:19,938
Oh, here, gotcha.

178
01:34:26,643 --> 01:34:26,843
Okay.

179
01:34:34,585 --> 01:34:34,845
[SPEAKER_01]: All right.

180
01:34:35,585 --> 01:34:35,706
[SPEAKER_01]: Okay.

181
01:34:35,826 --> 01:34:49,289
[SPEAKER_01]: Unified physical education brings students with and without disabilities together, fostering inclusion, respect and teamwork through shared physical activities, creating a supportive environment for all.

182
01:34:58,172 --> 01:34:59,954
[SPEAKER_37]: So why Unified PE?

183
01:35:00,554 --> 01:35:06,919
[SPEAKER_37]: It builds empathy and students learn to understand and appreciate differences while also connecting through similarities.

184
01:35:07,720 --> 01:35:09,141
[SPEAKER_37]: It increases activity.

185
01:35:09,161 --> 01:35:12,343
[SPEAKER_37]: Everyone participates, leading to improved health for all.

186
01:35:13,164 --> 01:35:14,184
[SPEAKER_37]: It improves community.

187
01:35:14,905 --> 01:35:20,489
[SPEAKER_37]: Unified PE fosters friendships and reduces isolation among peers, and it promotes teamwork.

188
01:35:20,569 --> 01:35:24,132
[SPEAKER_37]: Students collaborate, enhancing respect and communication skills.

189
01:35:32,154 --> 01:35:35,856
[SPEAKER_05]: So we have two videos to show you from what happens in our class.

190
01:35:36,177 --> 01:35:38,238
[SPEAKER_05]: There is no sound on it, so you just have to watch.

191
01:35:39,058 --> 01:35:40,479
[SPEAKER_05]: Oh, this is Hungry, Hungry Hippos.

192
01:35:40,579 --> 01:35:40,940
[SPEAKER_29]: That's right.

193
01:35:41,000 --> 01:35:42,120
[SPEAKER_29]: Human Hungry, Hungry Hippos.

194
01:35:53,808 --> 01:35:54,508
[SPEAKER_32]: No one's watching it.

195
01:35:55,789 --> 01:35:56,229
[SPEAKER_29]: You were there.

196
01:35:57,210 --> 01:35:58,091
[SPEAKER_29]: I saw Michael.

197
01:36:12,004 --> 01:36:14,005
[SPEAKER_29]: This is kind of like a human bowling.

198
01:36:14,625 --> 01:36:19,106
[SPEAKER_29]: We just worked on balancing on scooters and we got to knock stuff over.

199
01:36:19,166 --> 01:36:20,206
[SPEAKER_29]: Everyone likes to break things.

200
01:36:20,366 --> 01:36:20,627
[SPEAKER_32]: That's you.

201
01:36:20,667 --> 01:36:21,467
[SPEAKER_32]: I know her.

202
01:36:21,507 --> 01:36:22,747
[SPEAKER_32]: Are you sure about that?

203
01:36:29,847 --> 01:36:32,689
[SPEAKER_05]: We're going to have our students share some of their experiences.

204
01:36:38,934 --> 01:36:39,374
[SPEAKER_22]: All right.

205
01:36:39,394 --> 01:36:42,576
[SPEAKER_22]: I like playing basketball with my friends.

206
01:36:43,036 --> 01:36:46,119
[SPEAKER_22]: I like looking forward to seeing my friends in the gym.

207
01:36:46,579 --> 01:36:48,300
[SPEAKER_22]: It makes me feel great.

208
01:36:49,221 --> 01:36:50,162
[SPEAKER_22]: I like Unifying PE.

209
01:36:51,220 --> 01:36:55,549
[SPEAKER_22]: I like Unifying PE because I like to play basketball.

210
01:36:55,589 --> 01:37:01,682
[SPEAKER_22]: Coming to the Unifying PE class makes me happy and excited to play games like basketball and play football.

211
01:37:06,225 --> 01:37:10,627
[SPEAKER_32]: I like to see some of my friends.

212
01:37:11,467 --> 01:37:14,088
[SPEAKER_32]: We play basketball with other friends.

213
01:37:15,048 --> 01:37:15,708
[SPEAKER_32]: What the hell?

214
01:37:15,748 --> 01:37:16,148
[SPEAKER_32]: Sports.

215
01:37:16,768 --> 01:37:21,570
[SPEAKER_32]: But they get me to follow directions, show me how to do it.

216
01:37:22,750 --> 01:37:23,110
[SPEAKER_32]: Welcome.

217
01:37:29,172 --> 01:37:30,292
[SPEAKER_05]: Thank you.

218
01:37:31,313 --> 01:37:32,673
[SPEAKER_22]: Do you have any questions?

219
01:37:36,333 --> 01:37:38,974
[SPEAKER_14]: Which sport besides basketball did you like?

220
01:37:38,994 --> 01:37:40,754
[SPEAKER_14]: I heard you say basketball a few times.

221
01:37:42,375 --> 01:38:01,619
[SPEAKER_21]: I like to play flag football, and doing some juggling, and sports, and if you like, capture the chicken, the hungry, hungry hippo, and like, the hair man bowling.

222
01:38:01,639 --> 01:38:04,120
[SPEAKER_15]: Great, good answer.

223
01:38:05,669 --> 01:38:06,609
[SPEAKER_15]: Yep, member Graham.

224
01:38:07,149 --> 01:38:08,670
[SPEAKER_14]: Is everything else you want to ask?

225
01:38:08,690 --> 01:38:09,970
[SPEAKER_14]: Do you have any questions?

226
01:38:10,170 --> 01:38:12,050
[SPEAKER_14]: Yes, member Graham has a question for you.

227
01:38:12,470 --> 01:38:13,210
[SPEAKER_07]: I have a question.

228
01:38:13,290 --> 01:38:17,331
[SPEAKER_07]: I wondered if we could be invited the next time you play Hungry Hungry Hippos.

229
01:38:18,572 --> 01:38:19,152
[SPEAKER_21]: Can we come?

230
01:38:20,032 --> 01:38:21,132
[SPEAKER_21]: Can we come?

231
01:38:21,352 --> 01:38:22,972
[SPEAKER_07]: Can you let us know the next time you play?

232
01:38:23,012 --> 01:38:23,652
[SPEAKER_07]: Can we play with you?

233
01:38:23,673 --> 01:38:23,813
[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah.

234
01:38:23,833 --> 01:38:24,793
[SPEAKER_07]: Awesome, thank you.

235
01:38:31,614 --> 01:38:32,234
[SPEAKER_13]: Great, thank you.

236
01:38:33,495 --> 01:38:39,698
[SPEAKER_13]: Could I just, could the advisors, so I think you explained this at the beginning, but I just think it's important to note.

237
01:38:39,738 --> 01:38:43,760
[SPEAKER_13]: So Carla, Andre, do you mind explaining what your position is?

238
01:38:44,400 --> 01:38:52,104
[SPEAKER_13]: And then Macalusi, will you please explain what your position is so that everyone is aware, even joining at home, what the collaboration is like for this course?

239
01:38:52,364 --> 01:38:54,785
[SPEAKER_29]: Sure, so I'm a high school physical education teacher.

240
01:38:57,540 --> 01:39:00,220
[SPEAKER_29]: Yeah, that's my job.

241
01:39:00,240 --> 01:39:04,481
[SPEAKER_05]: I am the district-wide adapted physical education teacher, and I also am the unified coach.

242
01:39:05,501 --> 01:39:10,242
[SPEAKER_05]: And so like I said before, it is an initiative put forth by the Special Olympics that we've adopted into our district.

243
01:39:10,702 --> 01:39:18,184
[SPEAKER_05]: And unified PE kind of creates that opportunity, the accessibility for students who might not be able to participate in a sport after school.

244
01:39:18,544 --> 01:39:23,665
[SPEAKER_05]: It creates that whole school environment that the Special Olympics and unified really seeks to capture.

245
01:39:25,721 --> 01:39:26,602
[SPEAKER_13]: Perfect, thank you.

246
01:39:27,062 --> 01:39:28,844
[SPEAKER_13]: And Carla's position is district-wide.

247
01:39:29,364 --> 01:39:42,855
[SPEAKER_13]: So there's huge impact throughout the district, but this is just a really wonderful demonstration of what unified means to our students and our overall community for belonging.

248
01:39:42,895 --> 01:39:44,616
[SPEAKER_13]: So thank you both for everything you do.

249
01:39:45,137 --> 01:39:46,318
[SPEAKER_13]: And wonderful job.

250
01:39:46,578 --> 01:39:48,019
[SPEAKER_13]: Was there another question before we do a picture?

251
01:39:48,039 --> 01:39:49,340
[SPEAKER_13]: I think member Olopade has a question.

252
01:39:49,360 --> 01:39:51,142
[SPEAKER_36]: Just a quick question.

253
01:39:51,502 --> 01:39:52,242
[SPEAKER_36]: Thank you so much for this.

254
01:39:52,262 --> 01:39:52,923
[SPEAKER_36]: This is wonderful.

255
01:39:52,943 --> 01:39:55,385
[SPEAKER_36]: This is one of my favorite programs that we do here in the district.

256
01:39:56,005 --> 01:40:01,410
[SPEAKER_36]: The question for, I just, for the whole district and for families at home, is there an application process to get involved?

257
01:40:01,531 --> 01:40:02,832
[SPEAKER_36]: Is it student by student?

258
01:40:02,852 --> 01:40:06,976
[SPEAKER_36]: Like how do you guys roll that out so we can have more and more people join in the district?

259
01:40:18,290 --> 01:40:21,052
[SPEAKER_29]: With high school helpers, it's junior and seniors.

260
01:40:21,852 --> 01:40:22,973
[SPEAKER_29]: We go through course selection.

261
01:40:23,413 --> 01:40:25,314
[SPEAKER_29]: And we really want kids that want to be there.

262
01:40:26,575 --> 01:40:29,116
[SPEAKER_29]: With the CHOICE program, it's working great.

263
01:40:29,156 --> 01:40:32,718
[SPEAKER_29]: But sometimes if you have a kid that doesn't want to be there, it could be an obstacle.

264
01:40:32,858 --> 01:40:37,061
[SPEAKER_29]: But our high school helpers are tremendous.

265
01:40:37,521 --> 01:40:39,042
[SPEAKER_29]: We have some of the best kids in school.

266
01:40:39,102 --> 01:40:42,104
[SPEAKER_29]: Every last period, Tuesday, Thursday, it's one of the highlights of my week.

267
01:40:42,124 --> 01:40:42,304
[SPEAKER_29]: Awesome.

268
01:40:42,324 --> 01:40:42,824
[SPEAKER_29]: Awesome.

269
01:40:43,805 --> 01:40:44,305
[SPEAKER_29]: Thank you so much.

270
01:40:47,326 --> 01:40:47,506
[SPEAKER_28]: Yes.

271
01:40:47,627 --> 01:40:50,216
[SPEAKER_28]: And I was just wondering what this looks like at other schools.

272
01:40:51,681 --> 01:40:52,423
[SPEAKER_05]: That is a good question.

273
01:40:54,180 --> 01:40:59,644
[SPEAKER_05]: I think we are looking in the coming years to do this at the middle school level.

274
01:41:00,685 --> 01:41:12,434
[SPEAKER_05]: That would be, so we started with unified sports and now we have unified PE at the high school level and then we started with unified sports at the middle school level and so the next step would be unified PE at the middle school level.

275
01:41:12,814 --> 01:41:16,137
[SPEAKER_05]: So I'm hoping the next two years we'll get that going.

276
01:41:16,797 --> 01:41:20,040
[SPEAKER_28]: And is there any talk of kind of expanding it even beyond athletics?

277
01:41:21,091 --> 01:41:24,393
[SPEAKER_05]: Yeah, so I, in particular, I do the athletics.

278
01:41:25,493 --> 01:41:28,215
[SPEAKER_05]: So I guess, yeah, that would be outside my realm.

279
01:41:28,255 --> 01:41:30,716
[SPEAKER_05]: But I know that there's a Best Buddies program now.

280
01:41:30,876 --> 01:41:35,499
[SPEAKER_05]: And so I think we are expanding with inclusivity as a whole through Medford, which is great to see.

281
01:41:35,799 --> 01:41:39,861
[SPEAKER_28]: And we saw that the Best Buddies was our Mustang moment a few meetings ago.

282
01:41:41,842 --> 01:41:42,503
[SPEAKER_13]: Thank you so much.

283
01:41:42,563 --> 01:41:43,663
[SPEAKER_13]: We could get you those details.

284
01:41:43,703 --> 01:41:49,666
[SPEAKER_13]: I know that director Suzanne Fee is also, if it's not in place already, is working on unified art.

285
01:41:51,460 --> 01:41:54,007
[SPEAKER_13]: up at the high school, so we can get those specifics for you.

286
01:41:56,353 --> 01:41:56,974
[SPEAKER_13]: Ready for a picture?

287
01:43:26,807 --> 01:43:27,407
[SPEAKER_13]: OK.

288
01:43:28,988 --> 01:43:29,849
[SPEAKER_13]: Three times a charm.

289
01:43:29,889 --> 01:43:32,310
[SPEAKER_13]: There's one more Mustang moment.

290
01:43:34,311 --> 01:43:35,892
[SPEAKER_13]: It is our honor to welcome.

291
01:43:35,912 --> 01:43:46,419
[SPEAKER_13]: We're going to invite the adults up to talk about a Massachusetts youth contest that one of our students won.

292
01:43:46,439 --> 01:43:54,623
[SPEAKER_13]: So we're going to get a little bit of framing about what that contest was before we hear from the student about her why in.

293
01:43:56,457 --> 01:43:57,020
[SPEAKER_13]: her poster.

294
01:43:58,208 --> 01:43:58,349
[SPEAKER_13]: OK.

295
01:43:59,481 --> 01:44:00,021
[SPEAKER_04]: Good evening.

296
01:44:00,201 --> 01:44:01,162
[SPEAKER_04]: I'm Margie Daniels.

297
01:44:01,182 --> 01:44:04,844
[SPEAKER_04]: I'm the executive director of Massachusetts Partnerships for Youth.

298
01:44:05,425 --> 01:44:09,687
[SPEAKER_04]: We're a nonprofit organization that serves school districts across the Commonwealth.

299
01:44:09,767 --> 01:44:14,010
[SPEAKER_04]: And first of all, I want to thank you for the privilege of being here tonight in front of you.

300
01:44:14,850 --> 01:44:16,571
[SPEAKER_04]: You have such a wonderful school system.

301
01:44:17,092 --> 01:44:20,294
[SPEAKER_04]: And you've been so involved with our organization for many years.

302
01:44:21,114 --> 01:44:24,416
[SPEAKER_04]: We have a theme every year for a poster project.

303
01:44:24,476 --> 01:44:28,639
[SPEAKER_04]: And this year, our theme was kind people are the best kind of people.

304
01:44:29,499 --> 01:44:43,143
[SPEAKER_04]: And I'm happy to tell you we had 151 entries from across the Commonwealth, and to have an honorable mention in the Medford Public Schools is such an honor when there were so many students, and you have one.

305
01:44:43,663 --> 01:44:48,265
[SPEAKER_04]: So I'm here with very good news that we are recognizing Nora Shaw tonight.

306
01:44:48,285 --> 01:44:56,347
[SPEAKER_04]: Do you want to hold it?

307
01:44:57,148 --> 01:44:57,988
[SPEAKER_04]: Show them your picture.

308
01:44:58,812 --> 01:44:59,212
[SPEAKER_04]: Beautiful?

309
01:45:01,353 --> 01:45:01,573
[SPEAKER_04]: Yeah.

310
01:45:03,774 --> 01:45:04,174
[SPEAKER_04]: Thank you.

311
01:45:04,895 --> 01:45:06,675
[SPEAKER_04]: And we have a gift for you.

312
01:45:06,695 --> 01:45:07,756
[SPEAKER_04]: Would you like to unwrap it?

313
01:45:07,796 --> 01:45:09,056
[SPEAKER_04]: First, there's a certificate.

314
01:45:09,116 --> 01:45:14,599
[SPEAKER_04]: So open up the ribbon and take a look at the certificate first.

315
01:45:15,679 --> 01:45:18,901
[SPEAKER_04]: Maybe you could show the audience the people sitting here.

316
01:45:18,921 --> 01:45:26,344
[SPEAKER_32]: Thank you.

317
01:45:27,012 --> 01:45:30,473
[SPEAKER_04]: And maybe we could get a picture with you holding the certificate.

318
01:45:30,673 --> 01:45:33,074
[SPEAKER_04]: And please step up with us.

319
01:45:35,215 --> 01:45:36,896
[SPEAKER_13]: We can do a picture in one moment.

320
01:45:36,916 --> 01:45:42,858
[SPEAKER_13]: So I do want to say that we're joined by also Principal Skane and art teacher Pete Gallagher.

321
01:45:43,399 --> 01:45:49,161
[SPEAKER_13]: And I do want to, I'm not sure if any adults also want to speak or if we could hear from the student too.

322
01:45:51,802 --> 01:45:53,583
[SPEAKER_13]: Just speak into the microphone.

323
01:45:55,283 --> 01:45:55,604
Hold on.

324
01:45:56,943 --> 01:45:59,124
[SPEAKER_15]: I coached her when she was way little, way little.

325
01:45:59,344 --> 01:46:05,388
[SPEAKER_00]: So when I was working on this project, I was thinking about sometimes how all schools have positive posters.

326
01:46:06,028 --> 01:46:10,370
[SPEAKER_00]: And when I look at them, sometimes when I'm having a rough day, it does make my day better.

327
01:46:10,490 --> 01:46:11,691
[SPEAKER_00]: So I like seeing them.

328
01:46:12,191 --> 01:46:16,974
[SPEAKER_00]: And when I was working on my poster, I was trying to think about that and put that into my poster.

329
01:46:17,754 --> 01:46:19,075
[SPEAKER_00]: So thank you for having me.

330
01:46:26,185 --> 01:46:37,773
[SPEAKER_04]: And Nora, just so you know, the judges, our school superintendents, police chiefs, community members, school counselors, we have a very multidisciplinary group and they just loved your poster.

331
01:46:37,973 --> 01:46:38,973
[SPEAKER_04]: They thought it was beautiful.

332
01:46:39,234 --> 01:46:40,434
[SPEAKER_04]: Now there was something else there, huh?

333
01:46:40,454 --> 01:46:42,876
[SPEAKER_03]: This is a gift for you.

334
01:46:42,976 --> 01:46:43,677
[SPEAKER_03]: Where is my gift?

335
01:46:52,734 --> 01:46:53,214
[SPEAKER_32]: Thank you so much.

336
01:46:53,234 --> 01:46:53,855
[SPEAKER_04]: You're welcome.

337
01:46:54,135 --> 01:46:54,655
[SPEAKER_04]: You're welcome.

338
01:46:54,675 --> 01:46:56,636
[SPEAKER_04]: Maybe you'll buy some art supplies.

339
01:46:56,696 --> 01:46:57,777
[SPEAKER_04]: You're very talented.

340
01:46:59,217 --> 01:47:00,138
[SPEAKER_04]: So thank you again.

341
01:47:00,198 --> 01:47:01,859
[SPEAKER_04]: It's a pleasure to be here tonight.

342
01:47:02,619 --> 01:47:03,379
[SPEAKER_04]: Congratulations.

343
01:48:25,218 --> 01:48:25,639
[SPEAKER_15]: Wonderful.

344
01:48:32,329 --> 01:48:32,630
[SPEAKER_15]: Great.

345
01:48:37,357 --> 01:48:38,479
[SPEAKER_15]: Let's move through this.

346
01:48:38,499 --> 01:48:40,162
[SPEAKER_15]: Then it'll be dinner time.

347
01:48:41,857 --> 01:48:42,017
[SPEAKER_15]: Yep.

348
01:48:42,397 --> 01:48:47,320
[SPEAKER_15]: We are going to meet Ina Williams, our new district wide transportation director.

349
01:48:47,440 --> 01:48:51,442
[SPEAKER_15]: I'm going to turn it over to you, Dr. Galussi, for the official welcome.

350
01:48:52,022 --> 01:48:53,303
[SPEAKER_13]: Thank you so much.

351
01:48:53,523 --> 01:48:57,605
[SPEAKER_13]: Ina J. Williams is our new transportation manager.

352
01:48:58,326 --> 01:49:00,789
[SPEAKER_13]: I am so happy and thrilled.

353
01:49:01,510 --> 01:49:06,557
[SPEAKER_13]: Ina comes to us with a lot of expertise and experience in school transportation.

354
01:49:07,137 --> 01:49:12,425
[SPEAKER_13]: She has worked for Medway Public Schools, Asabet Valley Collaborative.

355
01:49:13,186 --> 01:49:15,489
[SPEAKER_13]: She has a lot of experience in which I think she'll be

356
01:49:16,149 --> 01:49:20,511
[SPEAKER_13]: able to make a lot of positive change and improvements for Medford Public Schools.

357
01:49:21,752 --> 01:49:30,656
[SPEAKER_13]: She has a wonderful way about her, and I think she's got a skill in building community, which is everything that Medford Public Schools is striving for.

358
01:49:30,796 --> 01:49:32,937
[SPEAKER_13]: So she's had a nice welcome.

359
01:49:33,598 --> 01:49:40,601
[SPEAKER_13]: She's been meeting with school leaders as well as our bus transportation partners, NRT and Eastern Bus.

360
01:49:41,041 --> 01:49:43,803
[SPEAKER_13]: And so I just wanted to have the opportunity to be able to

361
01:49:44,263 --> 01:49:48,005
[SPEAKER_13]: welcome her formally at the school committee meeting so you could all see her.

362
01:49:48,046 --> 01:50:01,154
[SPEAKER_13]: I think it's very important for the community to also have an introduction to Ina so that they can also see the face that's behind the phone call or the email sometimes as we know transportation goes.

363
01:50:01,875 --> 01:50:03,876
[SPEAKER_13]: So I don't know Ina if you.

364
01:50:04,550 --> 01:50:07,393
[SPEAKER_02]: So I just wanted to say thank you all for giving me the opportunity.

365
01:50:07,453 --> 01:50:09,675
[SPEAKER_02]: I'm really looking forward to working with the district.

366
01:50:09,775 --> 01:50:14,819
[SPEAKER_02]: As Dr. Lucia said, I've had the chance to meet with some of the bus vendors and the administrators.

367
01:50:14,979 --> 01:50:21,045
[SPEAKER_02]: And I've had a few students that have popped in to ask some questions that I was able to find the answers for rather quickly.

368
01:50:21,185 --> 01:50:22,886
[SPEAKER_02]: So I'm just really looking forward to it.

369
01:50:22,906 --> 01:50:25,609
[SPEAKER_02]: It's a wonderful community and a very welcoming environment.

370
01:50:26,930 --> 01:50:27,470
[SPEAKER_13]: Thank you so much.

371
01:50:27,490 --> 01:50:27,691
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

372
01:50:27,711 --> 01:50:28,311
[SPEAKER_13]: We're very excited.

373
01:50:28,331 --> 01:50:29,312
[SPEAKER_13]: Yeah, we're happy you're here.

374
01:50:29,332 --> 01:50:30,113
[SPEAKER_14]: Member Russo?

375
01:50:31,183 --> 01:50:32,163
[SPEAKER_31]: I just wanted to say thank you.

376
01:50:32,243 --> 01:50:51,369
[SPEAKER_31]: It's a really hard job, I'm sure you're well aware, so I'm very grateful that you're still smiling as well, which is, you know, when I hear about what this job is like, I'm just like, people have passions, not necessarily the same as everybody else, but I'm glad you're into it, so thank you.

377
01:50:51,549 --> 01:50:52,369
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you very much.

378
01:50:53,069 --> 01:50:53,549
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you all.

379
01:50:53,589 --> 01:50:54,349
[SPEAKER_02]: Have a good evening.

380
01:50:55,590 --> 01:50:56,230
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you very much.

381
01:50:59,503 --> 01:51:03,706
[SPEAKER_15]: And we have a report on the fiscal year 27 preliminary budget recommendations.

382
01:51:05,627 --> 01:51:08,789
[SPEAKER_15]: Noelle Velez, our Director of Finance, and Jerry McHugh, our Budget Analyst.

383
01:51:08,990 --> 01:51:10,390
[SPEAKER_15]: And welcome, come on up.

384
01:51:10,471 --> 01:51:11,872
[SPEAKER_15]: And I'll turn it over to Dr. Galluzzi.

385
01:51:13,232 --> 01:51:13,593
[SPEAKER_13]: Thank you.

386
01:51:13,633 --> 01:51:16,235
[SPEAKER_13]: I do just want to start with a little bit of framing.

387
01:51:16,275 --> 01:51:19,777
[SPEAKER_13]: So good evening, Honorable Members of School Committee and Madam Mayor.

388
01:51:20,457 --> 01:51:27,903
[SPEAKER_13]: So tonight's meeting serves to formally present our preliminary projections, expenditures, and identified school and department needs.

389
01:51:29,243 --> 01:51:39,130
[SPEAKER_13]: Our finance director, Noelle Velez, and our budget analyst, Jerry McHugh, will walk you through the results of extensive collaborative sessions with school and department leaders.

390
01:51:39,830 --> 01:51:51,397
[SPEAKER_13]: These meetings, as highlighted a little bit in the previous school committee meeting, were instrumental in identifying the critical needs and strategic requests that have emerged from our classroom and operations.

391
01:51:52,458 --> 01:52:07,944
[SPEAKER_13]: I want to stress that this is a deeply iterative process, and the data shared tonight will also highlight a range of initial asks that we're still actively reviewing, while the presentation will also show proactive areas that we've identified some meaningful savings.

392
01:52:08,565 --> 01:52:13,607
[SPEAKER_13]: Our team will also explain some unanticipated expenses that arose throughout this fiscal year.

393
01:52:15,122 --> 01:52:21,847
[SPEAKER_13]: And through this process, we will continue to refine and sharpen our budget projections and align our resources.

394
01:52:22,468 --> 01:52:30,894
[SPEAKER_13]: I think it also is important to note that with the new leadership team that has been working together this year at central office,

395
01:52:31,875 --> 01:52:36,358
[SPEAKER_13]: With that comes a little level of auditing within their respective portfolios.

396
01:52:37,258 --> 01:52:54,789
[SPEAKER_13]: And this initial review is anchoring the structural and visionary work required to ensure that our fiscal footprint allows authentically and intentionally with our district core values and the evolving needs of our students, our staff, and our community.

397
01:52:55,669 --> 01:53:07,976
[SPEAKER_13]: Although our work is far from finished, tonight's presentation is a testament to the consistency and coherence we are working to establish as through lines across every level of the district.

398
01:53:08,636 --> 01:53:13,980
[SPEAKER_13]: We're moving towards a unified vision that ensures every dollar supports our shared educational goals.

399
01:53:14,980 --> 01:53:27,047
[SPEAKER_13]: I really want to extend my sincere gratitude to Jerry and Noel for their tireless efforts and work in preparing the budget and for their commitment to transparency, as you will see this evening.

400
01:53:27,688 --> 01:53:39,435
[SPEAKER_13]: Their hard work, as well as everyone involved in this process, provides the solid foundation we need to move forward together to finalize a budget that serves all of our students and the community.

401
01:53:40,095 --> 01:53:40,976
[SPEAKER_13]: So thank you very much.

402
01:53:49,072 --> 01:53:51,053
[SPEAKER_12]: Oh, I'm sorry about that.

403
01:53:51,414 --> 01:53:53,295
[SPEAKER_12]: Thank you much, Superintendent, for those kind words.

404
01:53:53,315 --> 01:54:01,381
[SPEAKER_12]: I also want to give a special thanks to Lisa Malone and Joanne Allen, who scheduled approximately 57 meetings during this budget process.

405
01:54:02,341 --> 01:54:03,442
[SPEAKER_12]: So that was very kind of them.

406
01:54:03,502 --> 01:54:06,464
[SPEAKER_12]: And also to Dr. Talbot, who also attended a lot of our meetings with us.

407
01:54:06,804 --> 01:54:08,866
[SPEAKER_12]: Really appreciated that to give us a better insight.

408
01:54:09,793 --> 01:54:14,056
[SPEAKER_12]: of what finance and curriculum and how they are so important come together hand in hand.

409
01:54:14,896 --> 01:54:21,180
