518
02:10:01,304 --> 02:10:09,854
[SPEAKER_33]: is calculated to include 1.7% of the total budget for PD.

519
02:10:10,655 --> 02:10:18,004
[SPEAKER_33]: Now, schools aren't obligated to spend that much on PD, but it's just a benchmark.

520
02:10:21,366 --> 02:10:23,307
[SPEAKER_33]: asking for something that's much smaller here.

521
02:10:23,687 --> 02:10:35,694
[SPEAKER_33]: The other thing, the other part of this initiative is to distribute the implementation of the program of professional development

522
02:10:38,025 --> 02:11:04,675
[SPEAKER_33]: into the program so that directors are responsible for a program for their staff that's uniquely focused on their departments in order to better meet the needs of the staff that's in those departments.

523
02:11:06,339 --> 02:11:24,255
[SPEAKER_33]: Another data point is that 81% of our teaching staff are in step five or higher, so they're not having to participate in postgraduate courses and other courses to maintain or achieve their licensure.

524
02:11:24,335 --> 02:11:29,259
[SPEAKER_33]: So this is really going to be the only source of training for those teachers.

525
02:11:31,988 --> 02:11:39,290
